  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I work as deputy manager in a nationalised bank. I wank to work as an investment banker. I am a graduate. What courses should I do?",
  "response": "Transitioning from a deputy manager at a nationalised bank to an investment banker is an ambitious and rewarding path. Here's a structured plan that can help you achieve your goal:\n\n### Educational Courses\n1. **CFA (Chartered Financial Analyst)**\n   - A highly respected certification in the finance industry.\n   - Focuses on investment management skills, financial analysis, and portfolio management.\n\n2. **MBA in Finance**\n   - Many investment bankers hold an MBA, specifically with a concentration in finance.\n   - An MBA program from a top-tier business school can significantly enhance your knowledge and network.\n\n3. **Financial Modeling and Valuation**\n   - Various online platforms offer specialized courses in financial modeling and valuation.\n   - This skill is essential for investment banking as it involves creating models to value companies.\n\n4. **Certified Investment Banking Professional (CIBP)**\n   - This is a certification tailored for aspiring investment bankers.\n   - Courses offer practical knowledge and skills specific to investment banking.\n\n### Online Platforms and Institutes\n- **Coursera, Udemy, and edX**\n   - Offer various finance and investment banking courses from renowned institutions.\n   - Examples include courses on financial markets, corporate finance, and investment analysis.\n\n- **Investment Banking Institutes**\n   - Institutions like Wall Street Prep and Financial Edge offer specialized courses for investment banking.\n   - These courses are practical and career-focused.\n\n### Additional Steps\n1. **Networking**\n   - Attend industry conferences, webinars, and networking events.\n   - Connect with professionals in the investment banking industry through LinkedIn and other networking platforms.\n\n2. **Internships and Experience**\n   - Secure internships or short-term positions in investment banking firms.\n   - Hands-on experience is invaluable and can differentiate you from other candidates.\n\n3. **Stay Updated**\n   - Read finance-related newspapers, magazines, and journals.\n   - Follow market trends and understand the economic factors affecting investment banking.\n\n4. **Soft Skills Development**\n   - Enhance your negotiation, communication, and analytical skills.\n   - Investment banking requires a strong set of soft skills along with technical knowledge.\n\nBy strategically combining these education courses, certifications, and additional steps, you'll be well-prepared to make the transition to a successful career in investment banking.",
